title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J Kaiser Convention Center on 1988-02-13
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Apogee MiniMe (24bit/48k) -> Samplitude Professional v9.1.1 -> Adobe Audition v1.5 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket-> Sugaree, Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Mama Tried-> Big River, Loser

Set 2

Iko Iko, Looks Like Rain, Gimme Some Lovin'-> Jam*-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> One More Saturday Night-> Good Lovin'-> One More Saturday Night, E: Black Muddy River

*Without Jerry

reviews.review_text: 2-13-88 Decent show for a tour opener. A good remaster by C Miller. This is a matrix.

more interesting show than appears decently played first set w/ loser to close... didnt consider set 'warm-up' at all... nice LLR and a loose 2nd set... not intense, but loose... first show of 88 band sounds good :)
